<br>
Shame he is still wrong and AC isn't capped in the way implied.  It *is* capped in the way whatsit on this thread posted - capped for specific mobs and the way this works is due to the DI and DB.<br>
<br>
Someone wrote :-<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <br>
The more STR you have, the more your attack rating goes up. The more attack you have, the more often you hit a mob for max damage. So strength affects how often you hit for max, not what your max actually is. Please feel free to correct me<br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Your wrong.<br>
<br>
ATK is a *composite* figure.<br>
<br>
One half represents your chance &quot;To Hit&quot;.  This is *only* effected by your Level, Weapons Skill, Offense and any raw ATK buffs such as Wofl Form or Avatard.<br>
<br>
The other half represents your &quot;Maximum Damage&quot;.  This is effected by the above factors *and* Str.<br>
<br>
However, your Modal damage doesn't change with Strength, only your maximum, so the effect of Strength on average damage is minimal.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is that strength, like other stats in EQ, is worthless.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
