Here's some stuff that's slightly off topic, but it maybe somewhat relavent.  I'll get the actual logs out sometime (I'm a huge space cadet, so I tend to flake on follow ups =p) and see about DI and such.<br>
<br>
-------------------<br>
<br>
AC means piss vs. fungusbeasts =)<br>
<br>
Here's the breakdown.  Missing some exact numbers I have on notes at home (I'm at work atm), namely my exact AC, but I can ballpark it.  I have combat stability2 for this test.<br>
<br>
Test1 ( http://underwearninja.com/ytrilynth/images/fungus1.jpg ):  Doesnt mean much by itself, so we'll move on to Test2.  AC here was 1485ish<br>
<br>
Test2 ( http://underwearninja.com/ytrilynth/images/fungus2.jpg ): Exact same fungusbeast from test1.  Seeing some slight randomness, I probably didnt parse quite enough.  .25 difference in average damage. 1.6% difference in avoidance.  AC here was 1385ish.<br>
<br>
Test3 ( http://underwearninja.com/ytrilynth/images/fungus3.jpg ):  Still the same fungusbeast.  Notice I was getting bored, I didnt spend as much time on this one.  Mitigation still in the same range differing only by 1.23 from 200 AC higher.  AC here was 1285ish.<br>
<br>
Test4 (http://underwearninja.com/ytrilynth/images/fungus4.jpg ): This is where I @#%$ some @#%$ up.  I managed to die (lets not ask, k?) and when I got back, pulled a different beast.  This one had a higher max damage (most likely a higher level beast), but I parsed it anyway.  AC was about 1180.  Notice the Avg Damage is still about 70, despite the mob being higher level, and the most noticible difference in avoidance change is here, just over 2%.  Basically this set is junk because of the change in mob though.<br>
<br>
Test5 (http://underwearninja.com/ytrilynth/images/fungus5.jpg ):  Kill off the beast in Test4, and find one that maxes for 131 again.  I'm below 1100 AC, around 1080.  Virtually no change in Avg Damage, and virtually no change in Avoided damage. (assuming we throw out test 4)  At this point I've lost so many HPs, cleric was having a hard time keeping up the mana to CH me, and I was losing interest.  Hence the small sample size, but still consistent with other tests.<br>
<br>
Test6 (http://underwearninja.com/ytrilynth/images/fungus6.jpg ):  Under 1k AC.  Was about 975 I believe.  (yes, nine hundred seventy five).  Notice I switched beasts again.  Yeah I'm lame, sorry =/.  Luckily it's a 137 Hitter, so we can compare it to Test4.  Before we do that though, lets compare avoidance to Test5.  No change!  Higher level mob, lower AC, no decrease in Avoidance!  This is my smallest sample size, as I had about 1000 less hps, making mana regen an issue.  Despite the small sample, I think it's safe to say AC has little bearing for most purposes against Fungus Beasts for damage Avoidance.  This is the first noticable increase in damage intake, almost 4 points a hit higher than on the similar level mob in Test4.  I would have gone on farther, but I had already spent 5 hours at this, was getting kinda bored, and felt I had enough evidence to see a soft cap of some sort versus Fungus Beasts.<br>
<br>
Conclusion:  Hit Points are what counts for people when fighting Fungus Beasts.  My assumption is that all creatures in the same level range are going to show similar results.  I have yet to parse out another creature yet though.<br>
